data.description: At Lamphun (Northern Thailand) is a project to create a city inspired on ancient south-east Asian architecture. The artists who create the sculptures do so by head. They have no plan and they try to create something by only using their memory of what a statue could have looked like. The result are stunning sculptures and buildings. The location is Baan Phor Liang Meun or Thai Medicinal Plant Garden in Lamphun. When I was there in 2016 the entrance was free. Well worth a visit. Highly recommended.
